icon=\"gg\"]It can take between 30 minutes and two hours to feel the effects of an edible. Unlike smoking, which the effects can be felt almost instantly, an edible must be digested and make its way into your bloodstream to be felt. So, our advice is: be patient, start with a low dose, and wait for at least an hour so you know how the edible affects you before you ingest more.[/x_feature_box][x_feature_box title=\"I smoke marijuana frequently. That means my tolerance for edibles is high as well, right?\" title_color=\"\" text_color=\"\" graphic=\"icon\" graphic_size=\"60px\" graphic_shape=\"hexagon\" graphic_color=\"#ffffff\" graphic_bg_color=\"#2b7f27\" align_h=\"left\" align_v=\"top\" side_graphic_spacing=\"20px\" max_width=\"none\" child=\"true\" connector_width=\"1px\" connector_style=\"dashed\" connector_color=\"#272727\" graphic_icon=\"gg\"]No, not necessarily. Edibles need to be digested and then the chemicals need to get into your bloodstream before the effects are felt. This means that edibles can impact users differently than smoking. Everybody who is new to consuming edibles, even heavy marijuana users, should consume them with caution. Start with a small amount then wait some time and see how you feel before consuming more.\n[/x_feature_box][x_feature_box title=\"Should I eat before I consume an edible?\" title_color=\"\" text_color=\"\" graphic=\"icon\" graphic_size=\"60px\" graphic_shape=\"hexagon\" graphic_color=\"#ffffff\" graphic_bg_color=\"#2b7f27\" align_h=\"left\" align_v=\"top\" side_graphic_spacing=\"20px\" max_width=\"none\" child=\"true\" connector_width=\"1px\" connector_style=\"dashed\" connector_color=\"#272727\" graphic_icon=\"gg\"]Yes, as with many other kinds medications, it is recommended that edibles are consumed with food.[/x_feature_box][x_feature_box title=\"Can I get my medicine directly from you? Do you ship?\" title_color=\"\" text_color=\"\" graphic=\"icon\" graphic_size=\"60px\" graphic_shape=\"hexagon\" graphic_color=\"#ffffff\" graphic_bg_color=\"#2b7f27\" align_h=\"left\" align_v=\"top\" side_graphic_spacing=\"20px\" max_width=\"none\" child=\"true\" connector_width=\"1px\" connector_style=\"dashed\" connector_color=\"#272727\" graphic_icon=\"gg\"]No, we cannot sell our products directly to patients. We do not ship; and please be aware that is illegal to ship or carry cannabis products through the mail and across state lines.  We can only provide medicine to State of California licensed and registered collectives. Check out our Stash Finder to find our products near you![/x_feature_box][x_feature_box title=\"Copy of Copy of Copy of Copy of How long does it take to feel the effects of eating edibles?\" title_color=\"\" text_color=\"\" graphic=\"icon\" graphic_size=\"60px\" graphic_shape=\"hexagon\" graphic_color=\"#ffffff\" graphic_bg_color=\"#2b7f27\" align_h=\"left\" align_v=\"top\" side_graphic_spacing=\"20px\" max_width=\"none\" child=\"true\" connector_width=\"1px\" connector_style=\"dashed\" connector_color=\"#272727\" graphic_icon=\"gg\"]It can take between 30 minutes and two hours to feel the effects of an edible. Unlike smoking, which the effects can be felt almost instantly, an edible must be digested and make its way into your bloodstream to be felt. So, our advice is: be patient, start with a low dose, and wait for at least an hour so you know how the edible affects you before you ingest more.[/x_feature_box][/x_feature_list][/cs_column][/cs_row][/cs_section]', 'FAQs', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '37-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-12 06:40:20', '2016-01-12 06:40:20', '', '37', 'http://localhost:8888/wordpress_hashman/2016/01/12/37-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
